# Atomic Components

Organize UI under `src/components/` using atomic design:

```
src/components/
  atoms/       # Single-purpose primitives (Button, Input, Badge)
  molecules/   # Small compositions (NavLink, FormField, StatCard)
  organisms/   # Page sections (Header, Hero, ContactForm)
```

## Folder convention

- One component per folder: `atoms/Button/Button.js`
- Default export the component; colocate component-only styles/helpers in the same folder
- Import with the `@/` alias: `@/components/atoms/Button/Button`

## Reuse before create (required)

Before adding any component:

1. Search `src/components/` for atoms/molecules that already solve part of the need
2. Compose existing pieces instead of duplicating markup or styles
3. Only extract a new atom/molecule when the pattern is reused or clearly will be
4. After creating a component, scan siblings at the same atomic level for consolidation opportunities

```js
// ❌ BAD — new Header nav link markup when NavLink exists
<a className="text-sm font-medium text-muted ...">About</a>

// ✅ GOOD — compose existing molecule
import NavLink from "@/components/molecules/NavLink/NavLink";
<NavLink href="#about">About</NavLink>
```
